SIMPLE: shortly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shortly
<hw>Short"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>sceortlice</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a short or brief time
or manner; soon; quickly.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall grow jealous of you <qex>shortly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The armies came <qex>shortly</qex> in view of each other.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In few words; briefly; abruptly; curtly; <as>as, to
express ideas more <ex>shortly</ex> in verse than in
prose</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shortness</ent>⟦br⟧
